strategy: Transform the query to use two semi-joins (EXISTS) from pre-filtered items to each fact table independently. Pre-compute distinct qualifying keys from inventory with date_dim join to minimize intermed
what_worked: Applied decorrelate, single_pass_aggregation, early_filter achieving 1.18x speedup
why_it_worked: Correlated subqueries re-execute per outer row; converting to JOIN eliminates per-row overhead; Consolidating repeated scans into CASE aggregates reduces I/O from N scans to 1; Applying selective filters early reduces intermediate row counts before expensive operations
